{
  "texts": [
    "Our sample shows that the peak of the R EXT Hα distribution is at about 10 -6, which is one order of magnitude smaller than the values of R Hα (about 10 -5).",
    "By recognizing the prominent N II lines, the MRS spectra contaminated by the H II regions can be identified.",
    "Figure 15 shows an example MRS spectrum of the N II lines from H II regions, in which the Hα emission line of H II regions is located in between the two N II lines.",
    "The vacuum wavelengths of the two N II line are 6549.86 Å and 6585.27 Å, respectively (Stoughton et al, 2002).",
    "We calculate the mean fluxes in the central bands of the N II lines (6549.860 ± 0.125 Å and 6585.270 ± 0.125 Å, respectively, with band width being 0.25 Å), and then normalize the central fluxes by the fluxes in two nearby continuum bands."
  ]
}